The paper discusses the development of agents that can efficiently gather information through searching in a partially-observed environment. This involves the use of deep architectures and reinforcement learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CL. Additionally, the paper mentions shaping the behavior of the agents through extrinsic and intrinsic rewards, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.RO and cs.CV, respectively.
